===========================
How the Project was created:

1. Created using below maven archetype:
$ mvn archetype:generate -DarchetypeGroupId=org.apache.maven.archetypes -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-webapp -DarchetypeVersion=1.4
groudID: webrtc
artifactID: signaling_server

2. Added following in pom.xml:
Modified Compiler options as below:
<maven.compiler.source>1.8</maven.compiler.source>
<maven.compiler.target>1.8</maven.compiler.target>

3. Added javaee dependency as below with existing dependencies:

    <dependency>
        <groupId>javax</groupId>
        <artifactId>javaee-api</artifactId>
        <version>7.0</version>
        <scope>provided</scope>
    </dependency>

4. Removed index.jsp:
$ rm src/main/webapp/index.jsp

5. Created "java" directory where all our micro-service code will live:
$ mkdir src/main/java

5. Replaced existing content of web.xml file with below content:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>                                         
<web-app version="3.1"                                                         
         xmlns="http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee"                 
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee http://java.sun.com/xml/ns/javaee/web-app_3_1.xsd">
    <servlet>
        <servlet-name>javax.ws.rs.core.Application</servlet-name>              
    </servlet>
    <servlet-mapping>                                                          
        <servlet-name>javax.ws.rs.core.Application</servlet-name>              
        <url-pattern>/webapi/*</url-pattern>
    </servlet-mapping>
</web-app>

6. Written the source code for our microservice compiled and deployed the war file
$ mvn clean package

============================
How the project was deployed:

1. Start the glassfish server default domain "domain1":
$ /opt/glassfish4/bin/asadmin start-domain

2. Deploy the web archive file:
$ /opt/glassfish4/bin/asadmin deploy target/signaling_server.war

3. Once one is done with the application we should undeploy it as below:
# Note while undeploying just specify application name without the extension(.war)
$ /opt/glassfish4/bin/asadmin undeploy signaling_server

4. Finally make sure you stop the domain as well:
$ /opt/glassfish4/bin/asadmin stop-domain
